claim.claim-text:
1. A system for predicting gate reliability, comprising:
a set of test structures in an integrated circuit device, the test structures comprising a plurality of gates;
first means for stressing the test structures in a parallel mode configuration to obtain gate dielectric test site data such that each of the structures is stressed at different conditions until each structure exhibits a hard fail to obtain plural sets of breakdown data based thereon;
means for analyzing and conducting an operation of collapsing the plural sets of breakdown data into a single set to improve the statistical confidence of the test site data results;
second means for stressing the test structures in a product mode configuration according to a defined criteria in order to determine how many of the parallel mode hard fails are also product mode hard fails; and
means for using the test site data to predict gate reliability.
